{"article_id":"5NFWE4uFu7qo9STj","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"If tried and found guilty ,","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Lerner could serve up to a year in prison .","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"|","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"M.Scott Mahaskey/","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"GOP hits IRS ' Lerner with contempt","depth":3},{"id":5,"text":"The House voted to hold Lois Lerner in contempt of Congress , just three days before the anniversary of the day","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"the former IRS official ignited the tea party targeting furor .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"The Republican-led chamber voted largely along party lines 231-187 to place the woman","depth":12},{"id":8,"text":"who has become the face of the controversy","depth":12},{"id":9,"text":"in contempt","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"for refusing to answer House Republicans ' questions .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"Six Democrats voted with Republicans .","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"\" You don ' t get to use a public hearing","depth":15},{"id":13,"text":"to tell the public","depth":16},{"id":14,"text":"and press your side of the story","depth":16},{"id":15,"text":"and then invoke the Fifth , \"","depth":14},{"id":16,"text":"said Oversight Committee Chairman Darrell Issa","depth":15},{"id":17,"text":"( R-Calif. )","depth":15},{"id":18,"text":"on the House floor .","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"\" That is not how the Fifth Amendment is meant to be used .","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"It is a shield ;","depth":14},{"id":21,"text":"Lois Lerner used it as a sword . \"","depth":14},{"id":22,"text":"( Earlier on :","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"GOP dares W.H . to ignore Lerner contempt )","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"Democrats dismissed the process as political foreplay","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"designed for election season .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"\" Bringing this political circus , this witch hunt to the floor","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"purely because it polls well with your base","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"is ludicrous , \"","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"said Rep. Jim McGovern","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"( D-Mass . ) .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"Lerner ' s lawyer William Taylor said in a statement","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"that \" it is unfortunate that the majority party in the House has put politics before a citizen ' s constitutional rights. \"","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Lerner has said","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"she has broken no laws .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"The contempt citation now goes to the Justice Department ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"where the U.S. Attorney for the District of Columbia could bring the issue to court .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"The department would not respond to a request for comment","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"on whether it will proceed with the case -","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"but some experts are expecting it to kill the case","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"rather than haul Lerner to court .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"The House in a separate measure voted to call on Attorney General Eric Holder to appoint a special counsel","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"to probe the matter .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"If tried","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"and found guilty ,","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"Lerner could serve up to a year in prison","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"or face a fine of up to $ 100,000 ,","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"according to a Congressional Research Service report .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"The contempt charge also allows the House to arrest Lerner","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"and put her in a Capitol jail cell","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"until she complies with the subpoena or until the end of the 113th Congress","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"- a congressional power","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"not exercised since the early 20th century .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"Lerner is the former head of the tax-exempt division","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"that pulled conservative groups","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"applying for exemptions for additional scrutiny","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"if they used words like tea party , patriot , and 9/12 in their applications .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"House Republicans have chosen for now to forgo any civil contempt citation against Lerner","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"that ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"if won ,","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"would force her to testify before the House","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"- a strategy","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"that has confused some lawyers .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"The contempt citation hardly ends the IRS scandal ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"with nearly a half-dozen congressional investigations","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"expected to wrap up in the coming months .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"But it may be the last time","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Republicans have a shot","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"at hearing from Lerner ;","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"criminal contempt","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"if upheld in court","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"will not require Lerner to testify .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"At one point , the Oversight Committee and Lerner ' s lawyer William Taylor III , founding partner of Zuckerman Spaeder , were close to a deal","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"allowing Lerner to testify","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"without immunity in public","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"- but the agreement fell through .","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"Ever since Lerner broke news of the practice","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"following a planted question at a May 10 , 2013 , legal conference ,","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"she has become the target of Republican scorn .","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"Republicans initially looked to the White House ,","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"equating the scandal to Watergate","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"and calling it a scheme by President Barack Obama","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"to target his enemies .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"But","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"when no smoking gun appeared ,","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"they toned down that rhetoric .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"The Treasury inspector general for tax administration in the first official report on the scandal attributed the unfair practice to gross mismanagement","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"- not political bias .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"But since then , House Republicans have built a case around Lerner ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"accusing her of using her top IRS position for political mischief .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":179,"left":91,"right":178,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":91,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":178,"left":93,"right":177,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":93,"left":92,"right":4,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":92,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":163,"right":176,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":144,"right":162,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":122,"right":143,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":122,"left":118,"right":121,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":111,"right":117,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":111,"left":94,"right":110,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":110,"left":97,"right":109,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":96,"right":10,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":95,"right":9,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":95,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":107,"right":108,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":11,"right":106,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":10